The current Director General Lungisa Fuzile has said he wants to leave his post. JOHANNESBURG - The National Treasury says it s making progress in its quest to find a new director general to act under Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba.The current Director General Lungisa Fuzile has said he wants to leave his post.Following Fuzile s decision to leave the position of finance ministry director general, the decision about who will take over is being closely watched by investors.They are trying to work out which policies Gigaba is planning to implement.Now the Treasury says it has received over 30 applications for the post.It also says some of those applications are from people already working at the Treasury.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)